TITLE: New Mexico governor warns about 'serious' weekend fire weather
SUMMARY: New Mexico's governor warned residents on Friday ahead of what is expected to be a historic and dangerous weekend for fire weather. Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham encouraged people still in mandatory evacuation areas to leave as soon as possible.

TITLE: This Mother's Day, Mama Bears really want these three things
SUMMARY: As a millennial “Mama Bear” to four school-aged children, let me tell you what Mama Bears want more than anything else this Mother’s Day.

TITLE: Trump says he has 'transformed the face of the Republican Party' as he stumps for Oz in PA Senate primary
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump spoke Friday in Pennsylvania in support of senatorial candidate Dr. Mehmet Oz.

TITLE: West Virginia flooding kills 1, governor declares State of Preparedness
SUMMARY: West Virginia streets flooded Friday after several inches of heavy rain fell in and around the Ohio River community. Fox Weather reported that one person was killed and several others were rescued in the event.

TITLE: Alabama prison fugitives Casey White, Vicky White 'would be fools to leave the country:' longtime USMS exec
SUMMARY: Investigators are likely turning Vicky White’s "world upside down" as they intensify their manhunt for the fugitive corrections officer and the prison escapee, Casey Cole White, who disappeared from an Alabama facility more than a week ago, says longtime U.S. Marshal Service commander Lenny DePaul.

TITLE: Russia moves forces to Mariupol ahead of 'Victory Day' parade, officials work to rescue trapped troops
SUMMARY: Russia is moving troops from combat zones in Ukraine to Mariupol in preparation for Russian President Vladimir Putin’s “Victory Day” parade in the southern port city, Ukraine’s Main Directorate of Intelligence of the Ministry of Defense warned Saturday.

If you're not heading to Louisville for the 148th "Run for the Roses," you can still get into race-day spirit with a mint julep, a hot brown and a fancy hat. TITLE: Clarence Thomas references Roe v. Wade draft opinion leak, says Supreme Court can't be 'bullied'
SUMMARY: Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas dismissed the idea of pressuring the court for desirable outcomes at a judicial conference Friday.

TITLE: Johnny Depp v. Amber Heard defamation trial: This week's craziest and most disturbing moments
SUMMARY: There was no shortage of explosive moments during the fourth week of Johnny Depp’s defamation trial against ex-wife Amber Heard, who took the stand in her own defense and accused the actor of repeated sexual assaults.

TITLE: 5 college graduation speeches that shocked students and parents alike
SUMMARY: Will Ferrell, Steve Jobs and three others left a lasting impression on new college grads when they delivered their commencement addresses — here's why.

TITLE: 7 secrets of Kentucky Derby racehorses
SUMMARY: At the Kentucky Derby on Saturday the sleek muscled dark bay, grey and chestnut thoroughbreds lining up will run one and quarter miles in just over two minutes as 170,000 fans cheer.

TITLE: New York man sentenced to 27 years to life after killing, dismembering woman then putting her remains in bags
SUMMARY: A jury in New York found Daquan Wheeler guilty of killing and dismembering a woman in 2018, and sentenced him to 27 years to life in prison during a hearing on Friday.

TITLE: Elon Musk's mom slams NYT over story suggesting he was 'detached from apartheid’s atrocities' in South Africa
SUMMARY: Elon Musk's mother criticized The New York Times this week after the newspaper claimed in a recent story that her son was "detached from apartheid’s atrocities" during his youth in South Africa.

TITLE: Germany announces ban on Ukrainian flags during WWII Victory Day parade: 'Slap in the face'
SUMMARY: German authorities have warned residents who attend the Victory Day military parade celebrations in Berlin not to bring Ukrainian or Russian flags.

TITLE: Michigan car owner sued after Jeep kills mechanic during oil change
SUMMARY: A Michigan man who left his car at a dealership for an oil change and tire rotation is being sued after his vehicle killed a mechanic.

TITLE: Jeopardy champion's 23-day winning streak ends after losing by $1
SUMMARY: Jeopardy champion Mattea Roach saw her 23-game streak end Friday after losing the final match by a single dollar.

TITLE: North Korea tests suspected submarine-launched missile
SUMMARY: North Korea fired a suspected ballistic missile Saturday, continuing a provocative streak in nuclear-capable demonstrations.

TITLE: Solo climber missing for nearly a week found dead in Alaska
SUMMARY: The body of a solo climber who has been missing for nearly a week has been found at the Denali National Park in Alaska, but search teams will not be able to attempt a rescue attempt for at least another week.

TITLE: Severe weather topples wall at North Carolina facility
SUMMARY: A wall at a North Carolina distribution center was ripped apart by a severe storm on Friday, but no injuries have been reported.

TITLE: North Carolina food bank describes 'definite' impact of baby formula shortage
SUMMARY: The baby formula shortage in the U.S. is negatively impacting some food banks and pantries that serve lower-income clients. Derrick Williams, operations manager for the Food Bank of Central and Eastern North Carolina in Raleigh, N.C., said its food bank is "definitely being impacted" by the shortage. Meanwhile, a pediatrician warns parents against trying to make their own infant formula at home.
